The paper proposes a machine vision method using deep learning architecture for defect detection and marking on leather. This involves image processing techniques and mathematical derivation of geometry. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of deep learning also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and metrics to evaluate the effectiveness of the proposed approach, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
